snippet.textDisplay: I love how you actually are able to go so far into proving how stories "Everybody knows about" often have no primary sources and are simply folklore. there was a story about an orphanage by me that burned down, some say with kids inside, some say because of their ghosts. the road is named after the orphanage, the boyscout camp nearby has a trail named after it. EXCEPT there's no record of an orphanage being located on that road, in fact there was an orphanage several miles away but was torn down, but the story is great, and still gets repeated around camp fires

snippet.textDisplay: Maybe don't update Wikipedia if you find something? Post about it somewhere else instead, thus creating a secondary source that Wikipedia can cite or a primary source that others can report on.

snippet.textDisplay: On the insane side, since we are discussing bizarre schemes: The Stealth No Royalty Oil Rig in the Oil Boom Area Scheme. The standard oil and gas drilling pipe is 32 feet, so it would be possible to fit a stealth drilling rig in the shell of the building and place the engine to run the turntable and hoist in the short building next to it.  It would be necessary to move the product through a pipe to a line where it could be removed disguised as a water or sewer line. While this would be almost impossible to pull off, it might be possible to convince a group of shady businessmen to invest in a stealth oil well - A crook tricking other crooks.
